Description: CVE-2026-0861 - Fix memalign alignment overflow check
 The change to cap valid sizes to PTRDIFF_MAX inadvertently dropped the
 overflow check for alignment in memalign functions. This patch reinstates
 the overflow check in _int_memalign for the alignment parameter, preventing
 potential heap corruption when passing too large an alignment with specific
 size parameters positioned near PTRDIFF_MAX.
Origin: upstream, commit:c9188d333717d3ceb7e3020011651f424f749f93
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33796
Author: Siddhesh Poyarekar <siddhesh@gotplt.org>
Last-Update: 2026-01-17

--- a/malloc/malloc.c
+++ b/malloc/malloc.c
@@ -4948,7 +4948,7 @@ _int_memalign (mstate av, size_t alignment, size_t bytes)


   nb = checked_request2size (bytes);
-  if (nb == 0)
+  if (nb == 0 || alignment > PTRDIFF_MAX)
     {
       __set_errno (ENOMEM);
       return NULL;
